text: Hey guys, it’s Ro!

The next treat that we’re gonna be making
are some Sweet Potato Doggie Biscuits!

The things you will need, will be: A cutting
board, some parsley, enough for

1/4 a cup finely minced, some celery, enough
for 1/2 a cup finely minced,

A medium sweet potato, you’re gonna need
about 3/4 of mashed sweet potato.

1 cup of brown rice flour, 1/4 cup of chicken
broth, 1 cup of oat flour,
1/2 a teaspoon of chicken seasoning.
A potato masher, a vegetable peeler a

small bone cookie cutter, this one is 3-1/2
inches and a mini bone cookie cutter,
this one is 1-3/4 inch.

The first thing that we’re gonna do to make
these doggie biscuits, is we are gonna
prep our sweet potato.

In front of me I’ve got a cutting board,
a knife, a peeler
and you want to peel your potato first.
So we're gonna peel off all the skin.

Then, take a sharp cutting knife, I like to
cut off the top and the bottom.

Then I’m gonna cut it hot dog way, right
down the middle.

And now I’m gonna flip them like this, and
cut ‘em one more time, down the middle.
Next I’m gonna cut them into cubes.
Put them into a medium saucepan and then

Fill your pan with water until the potatoes
are
covered and turn your heat to medium high. Then, cover with a lid.
Bring them to a boil and then.

cook for an additional 5-6 minutes after they’re
boiling.

You want to cook them until the potatoes are

Then remove from heat and carefully drain
the potatoes in the sink.

Potatoes are hot off the stove, I just strained

Now we’re gonna take our potato masher and

Celery is pretty easy to chop and to cut,

the bottom.

Once you have little slices, now we’re

Then we’re gonna mince our parsley, same

In a large bowl we are gonna combine our celery,

In a smaller bowl, we are gonna combine our
oat flour, brown rice flour,

Now we’re gonna pour our dry ingredients

the tray to sit there for an additional 30

The next treat that we’re gonna make are
PB & Carrot Mini Pup Cakes!
The perfect treat for a dogs birthday!

The things you will need, will be: A cutting
board, some carrots, you’ll need

enough to fill 1/4 a cup when shredded, plus
a little extra for decoration.

1/2 a cup of ground oat flour, 1/4 cup of
creamy peanut butter, 2 tablespoons

of coconut oil, 1/4 a cup of apple sauce,
2 tablespoons of one and 1/2 a teaspoon

of baking soda, 1/2 a cup of yogurt, 1/2 a
cup of peanut butter.

You will also need a mini cupcake tray, a
decorating bag fitted with a #22 tip.
And, mini cupcake liners.

First thing that we’re gonna do is get our
carrots ready to shred, in front of

me I’ve got a cutting board, sharp cutting
knife and, the peeler!

I’m gonna hold my carrot the long way and

To make dog safe frosting!

Ta-da!

Here are all the DIY Dog Treat Recipes that
we made today!

We made: Mini Mutt Mints, Sweet Potato Doggie
